title: PW$_{12}$O$_{40}\cdot$3H$_{3}$O Structure
comments:
This is a partially dehydrated version of \href{current_web_home_dir/A29B40CD12_cF656_227_ae2fg_e3g_b_g-001}{H$_{3}$PW$_{12}$O$_{40}$ $\cdot$ 29H$_{2}$O ($H4_{21}$)} and \href{current_web_home_dir/A5B40CD12_cP116_224_bd_e3k_a_k-001}{H$_{3}$PW$_{12}$O$_{40}$ $\cdot$ 5H$_{2}$O ($H4_{16}$)} or \href{current_web_home_dir/A27B52CD12_cP184_224_dl_eh3k_a_k-001}{H$_{3}$PW$_{12}$O$_{40}$ $\cdot$ 6H$_{2}$O}. The six H$_{5}$O$_{2}^+$ ions of the later structure have been replaced by three H$_{3}$O$^+$ ions. 
 The ICSD entry classifies the H$_{3}$O$^+$ ions as oxygen atoms, labeling them ``O5.''
